Package com.tdc.coin

Class CoinDispenserGold

java.lang.Object
com.tdc.AbstractComponent<CoinDispenserObserver>
com.tdc.coin.AbstractCoinDispenser
com.tdc.coin.CoinDispenserGold
All Implemented Interfaces:
ICoinDispenser, IComponent<CoinDispenserObserver>, Sink<Coin>, Source<Coin>
public final class CoinDispenserGold extends AbstractCoinDispenser implements Sink<Coin>
Represents a component that stores coins of a particular denomination to dispense them as change. This component can be automatically refilled from its source.
Author:
TDC, Inc.

  • Method Details

    • receive

      public void receive(Coin coin) throws CashOverloadException, DisabledException
      Causes the indicated coin to be added into the dispenser. If successful, announces "coinAdded" event. If a successful coin addition causes the dispenser to become full, announces "coinsFull" event. Requires power.
      Specified by:
      receive in interface Sink<Coin>
      Overrides:
      receive in class AbstractCoinDispenser
      Parameters:
      coin - The cash to place in the sink.
      Throws:
      DisabledException - If the coin dispenser is currently disabled.
      SimulationException - If coin is null.
      CashOverloadException - If the coin dispenser is already full.
